   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Before Save</uicontrol> event is executed when you click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol> or <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save &amp; Continue</uicontrol> and the logic is executed before you save the event. This event is used to validate the conditions before the form is saved.</p>
      <p product="Include_PG_Content" class="- topic/p ">
         <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Use Case# Validate if the value of a field exceeds the acceptable limits</uicontrol>
      </p>
      <p product="Include_PG_Content" class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Request For Proposal</uicontrol> (RFP) form, if you want a validation message to display if the total amount of the RFP is more than 20% of the total contract cost, then you can use the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Before Save</uicontrol> event to define the acceptable range of a value for the appropriate field.</p>
      <p product="Include_PG_Content" class="- topic/p ">
         <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Use Case# Insert or update fields in a form from another form based on defined condition</uicontrol>
      </p>
      <p product="Include_PG_Content" class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Expenses</uicontrol> form, if you want to update the records with the rows from the pay items of the associated Purchase Order (PO), then you can use the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Before Save</uicontrol> event to define the conditions.</p>
